/shrug I have always been a big fan of the genre. I played D&D long before I played any video game version of it. One of the things that had great appeal for me about EQ was that in D&D, how much immersion you had in the adventure was completely dependant on the imagination of the DM and the rest of your party (which was often times difficult to come by). But EQ took care of most of the imagination for me. I see this quality in most games that come out these days. So, I don't really see any one game as being 'the one' to replace EQ, just a fancier version of it.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="font-style: italic">That is all I have to say about that! - Forest Gump</span>
