                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not everyone hated it.  Just like any other game out there, you're going to have a fair share of whining, moaning and complaining, and like everything else, the bitching is what you'll remember most - not the good.
<br />

<br />
When "The Vision" went away, is about the time EQ started going down hill.  At least Brad and team had the guts to stick by what they envisioned the game to be to begin with instead catering and pandering to the whiners, which is a far cry from what the current development team seems to be doing,,,, IMHO.   
<br />

<br />
As for thinking the original EQ team was better than the team now....  I suppose it's all a matter of personal preference and perspective.   However, based on the fact that the original development team were the ones that actually thought up, developed,  and implemented EQ, I'd say there were better in quite a few aspects, especially, but not limited to, creativity.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
