                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">While I agree that "The Vision" got a lot of criticism (some justified, and some because The Vision is not Everyman's Vision), what it lent my early EQ experience was a sense of cohesiveness. There was an overarching structure, and the storylines made sense and were interwoven. It felt more like a unified whole. Since SOE took over, they have dismantled, destroyed, cobbled and patched, and otherwise broken up that cohesiveness. Entire lore lines ignored or contradicted, new ones inelegantly grafted on, etc. What I hope Vanguard will achieve is to remain cohesive. That alone makes me interested this far in advance. I may find I don't like Brad's new Vision. But I long for a world where there is a Vision. Does that make any sense?
<br />

<br />
Lomeloth</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
