                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">[quote]You are confusing bad game mechanics with a Vision. I played a High Elf paladin when EQ1 launched, and no class/race combo was so screwed at the time, with the penalties etc.[/qupte]
<br />

<br />
Pft. Paladins were in pretty good shape when EQ launched, since they were basically warriors who could heal themselves if needed, having, effectively, the same HPs, Armor and weapon choices as warriors, along with a set of spells.  If you want to talk about race/classes that were screwed try human rogues - humans had no advantages other than having no "bad" stats (balanced by having no -good- stats) and rogues were a "DPS" class with no way to mitigate the aggro or damage of doing more DPS than the tank.  They had many abilities that had been supposed to be the reason for their class, but which were either broken, or useless.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like spot on "vision" for the class right there. Kinda like warriors, in fact.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">
<br />
